 by Yitzhak Arad to guide readers through the events at Ponary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xLithuaniaxVilnius. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zLithuaniazVilnius. 0aJewsxPersecutionsxLithuaniaxVilnius. 0aJewsxPersecutionszLithuaniazVilnius. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocities. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aArad, Yitzhak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArad, Yitzhak, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMargolis, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeinbaum, Laurence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012917540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129175423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129175/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles